The paper describes the architecture of an intelligent decision system for evaluating corporate research and development projects and portfolios. This involves constructing an influence diagram model for individual research projects, which suggests a focus on artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG) techniques. The system's interactive approach and emphasis on flexibility also suggest a potential fit with research in social and information sciences (cs.SI), software engineering (cs.SE), and cybersecurity (cs.CY).
